* {{audio|en-us-conjunction.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{hyphenation|con|junc|tion|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ʌŋkʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of joining, or condition of being joined.
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} [[sexual intercourse|Sexual intercourse]].
#*{{RQ:Flr Mntgn Essays}}, vol.1. ch.29:
#*: Certaine Nations (and amongst others, the Mahometane) abhorre '''Conjunction''' with women great with childe.
# {{context|grammar|lang=en}} A word used to join other words or phrases together into sentences. The specific conjunction used shows how the two joined parts are related. ''Example: Bread, butter '''and''' cheese.''
# {{context|astronomy|lang=en}} The alignment of two bodies in the [[solar system]] such that they have the same [[longitude]] when seen from Earth.
# {{context|astrology|lang=en}} An [[aspect]] in which planets are in close proximity to one another.
# {{context|logic|lang=en}} The [[proposition]] resulting from the combination of two or more propositions using the [[∧]] (<math>\and</math>) [[operator]].

